{
  "texts": [
    "The authors also evaluated A3C on the MuJoCo physics simulator domain (Todorov et al. 2012).",
    "Many relevant improvements in DQN-based methods approach different aspects.",
    "Although DDQN addresses the overestimation bias of Q-learning and (as a consequence) of DQN, PER improves data efficiency in experience replaying.",
    "The Dueling Network improved the generalization across actions by representing state values and action advantages separately.",
    "A3C shifts the bias-variance trade-off by learning from multistep bootstrap targets and helps to propagate newly observed rewards faster to earlier visited states."
  ]
